Class GraphitiShapeEditPart

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable, org.eclipse.gef.EditPart, org.eclipse.gef.GraphicalEditPart, org.eclipse.gef.RequestConstants, IFeatureProviderHolder
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ShapeEditPart
    public abstract class GraphitiShapeEditPart
extends org.eclipse.gef.editparts.AbstractGraphicalEditPart
implements IFeatureProviderHolder
    This is an abstract marker class that indicates that an EditPart is a Graphiti edit part for a shape. It can e.g. be used to register an IAdapterFactory against Graphiti edit parts. This is useful e.g. for providing standard property sheets (or org.eclipse.ui.views.properties.tabbed.AdvancedPropertySections inside tabbed property sheets) for a selection in the Graphiti IDiagramContainerUI; simply use this class as for the adaptableType attribute of the adapter factory definition in plugin.xml.

    Introduced as part of the fix for Bugzilla 341898.

    Since:
    0.9
